  "prompt": "Does Donald Trump use Quora?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, there is no public evidence to suggest that Donald Trump actively uses Quora. Donald Trump has been known to engage with his audience primarily through other social media platforms, such as Twitter (now rebranded as X) before his account was suspended. After that, he launched his own social media platform, Truth Social, to communicate directly with his followers.\n\nQuora, being a platform focused on questions and answers, doesn't appear to be among the primary channels Donald Trump uses for communication or public engagement. However, discussions and content related to him may exist on Quora, contributed by other users seeking information or sharing opinions about his policies, actions, and public persona.\n\nIt's always possible that his or his team\u2019s use of various platforms could change, so for the most current information, you might want to check the latest sources or official statements.",
